        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 2:43PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 242 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Troy, or 7 miles north of Temple, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Golinda, Marlin, Pendleton, Otto, Mooreville, Riesel, Asa, Troy,
Perry, Mart, Bruceville-Eddy, Durango, Satin, Cego, Belfalls,
Chilton, Lake Creek Lake, McClanahan, Tomlinson Hill, and White Hall.

This includes Interstate 35 between mile markers 301 and 319.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
